.TH "ir_update_mapping" 9 "ir_update_mapping" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ir_update_mapping \- set a keycode in the scancode->keycode table
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" ir_update_mapping
.BI "(struct rc_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "struct rc_map *rc_map "  ","
.BI "unsigned int index "  ","
.BI "unsigned int new_keycode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the struct rc_dev device descriptor
.IP "rc_map" 12
scancode table to be adjusted
.IP "index" 12
index of the mapping that needs to be updated
.IP "new_keycode" 12
the desired keycode
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine is used to update scancode->keycode mapping at given
position.
.SH "RETURN"
previous keycode assigned to the mapping
